{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "In contrast to the above distillation-based variants of BERT, Lan et al.",
    "proposed the ALBERT [151] model, which has a significantly smaller size and improves the speed of inferences.",
    "Note that ALBERT mainly changes the model architecture through factorized embedding parameterization, cross-layer parameter sharing, and inter-sentence loss of coherence.To reduce the temporal complexity of inference in the two-input case from quadratic to linear, TwinBERT [129] uses twin-structured BERT-like encoders to encode the query and the document, respectively, and a crossing layer to combine the two embeddings and produce a similarity score.",
    "In contrast to BERT, the document representations in it are precomputed and stored via offline caching.",
    "Due to the success of the knowledge distillation technique, the training of TwinBERT is based on the teacher-student framework."
  ],
